        "content": "I’ve executed the full process as requested:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09B_temp` with all rows from `decision_table` where `TOUR` starts with `J09B`.\n2. Added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column and populated it:\n   - Houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` were set to `EVU`.\n   - For all other houses, `ENTSCHEIDUNG` was set to:\n     - `KSA` if the house has fewer than 3 distinct `EQUNR`.\n     - `EVU` otherwise.\n\n3. Enriched the data:\n   - Joined with `eablg` on `Installation` = `ANLAGE` to get the meter reading document number.\n   - Joined with `net_master` and `sales_master` on `EQUNR`.\n   - When both net and sales records existed, I used the sales_* fields (and effectively ignored the net_* values for the exported columns). When only net data existed, those values were kept.\n\n4. Exported the final result to a CSV named `J09B.csv` with exactly these columns:\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n\n   The file path is:\n   `sessions/gpt-5.1/processadaptation_0_values_processadaptationmethod_classic_tour_J09B_seed_4506/J09B.csv`\n\n5. Sent the CSV as an email attachment to `meter.readings@evu.com` with a brief cover note.\n\n6. Dropped the `J09B_temp` table from the database.\n\nIf you want, I can also provide the exact SQL used for each step for documentation or reuse.",
